OL,4,CScotland ahead of visit to Glasgow
OL,6,FA zero-hours contract is a type of
OL,7,Femployment that allows companies to
OL,8,Fonly pay staff when they need them. It
OL,9,Fcan see workers called at short notice
OL,10,Fto work a variety of hours, rather
OL,11,Fthan a set amount each week like most
OL,12,Fstaff.
OL,14,FLabour's changes would give workers
OL,15,Fthe right to a contract that matches
OL,16,Fthe number of hours they usually work
OL,17,Fand would require firms to give
OL,18,Freasonable notice and compensation if
OL,19,Fshifts are altered or cancelled.
